          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1646746946244-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add your <strong>plum chutney</strong>, <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>cornflour </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>to the bowl with the <strong>reserved five-spice marinade</strong></p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and mix well<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>plum mix</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>plum mix</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until reduced to a glossy sauce – this is your <strong>plum sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
